      • finish

        public R finish(java.util.Collection<? extends OutputWriter<O>> writers)
         throws java.io.IOException
        Description copied from class: Output
        Returns a result to be made available through MapReduceResult.getOutputResult().

        This method allows the Output to inspect the final state of its OutputWriters to produce a final result object. For example, if the OutputWriters produce blobs in blobstore, finish could collect and return a list of blob IDs.

        Should return null if no such result makes sense for this kind of output.

        Called after all OutputWriters have been closed (with OutputWriter.close()). It is possible for this method to be called more than once with the same writers collection. It is also possible for the job to fail after this is invoked.

        The writers argument will contain the same writers that Output.createWriters(int) returned in the same order. Writers may be serialized and deserialized multiple times. typically, getWriter will have been called in a different JVM.

        Specified by:
        finish in class Output<O,R>
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
